<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="400" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,580,2009]" pageId="1" pageNumber="400">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,580,605]" pageId="1" pageNumber="400">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Head (
<figureCitation box="[356,458,580,605]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 8" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1892,1915]" captionTargetBox="[288,1361,209,1838]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[205,1368,193,1843]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 8. Portanus restingalis sp. nov. Male holotype: 1, dorsal habitus (antennae and legs not depicted; right forewing partially damaged); 2, head, pronotum, and mesonotum, dorsal view; 3, pygofer, valve and left subgenital plate, lateral view; 4, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view (setae omitted); 5, right style, lateral view; 6, apical portion of right style, dorsal view; 7, connective and aedeagus, lateral view; 8, connective and aedeagus, ventral view. Abbreviations: C = connective, S = shaft of aedeagus, P = process of aedeagus. Scale bars in mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/258152/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="400">Figs 1, 2</figureCitation>
) with conspicuous pair of transverse dark brown stripes anteriorly, one above and one below ocelli; aedeagus (
<figureCitation box="[421,519,615,640]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 8" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1892,1915]" captionTargetBox="[288,1361,209,1838]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[205,1368,193,1843]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 8. Portanus restingalis sp. nov. Male holotype: 1, dorsal habitus (antennae and legs not depicted; right forewing partially damaged); 2, head, pronotum, and mesonotum, dorsal view; 3, pygofer, valve and left subgenital plate, lateral view; 4, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view (setae omitted); 5, right style, lateral view; 6, apical portion of right style, dorsal view; 7, connective and aedeagus, lateral view; 8, connective and aedeagus, ventral view. Abbreviations: C = connective, S = shaft of aedeagus, P = process of aedeagus. Scale bars in mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/258152/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="400">Figs 7, 8</figureCitation>
) ventrally with basally articulated, long bifid process.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="400" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,580,2009]" pageId="1" pageNumber="400">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,463,652,677]" pageId="1" pageNumber="400">Measurements (mm).</emphasis>
Male 
<typeStatus box="[554,657,652,677]" pageId="1" pageNumber="400">holotype</typeStatus>
: body length 6.90; crown length 0.56; transocular width 1.47; interocular width 0.72; maximum pronotal width 1.43; forewing length 5.40.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,580,2009]" pageId="1" pageNumber="400">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,724,749]" pageId="1" pageNumber="400">Description.</emphasis>
Head (
<figureCitation box="[434,543,724,749]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 8" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1892,1915]" captionTargetBox="[288,1361,209,1838]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[205,1368,193,1843]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 8. Portanus restingalis sp. nov. Male holotype: 1, dorsal habitus (antennae and legs not depicted; right forewing partially damaged); 2, head, pronotum, and mesonotum, dorsal view; 3, pygofer, valve and left subgenital plate, lateral view; 4, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view (setae omitted); 5, right style, lateral view; 6, apical portion of right style, dorsal view; 7, connective and aedeagus, lateral view; 8, connective and aedeagus, ventral view. Abbreviations: C = connective, S = shaft of aedeagus, P = process of aedeagus. Scale bars in mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/258152/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="400">Figs 1, 2</figureCitation>
) with median length of crown slightly less than 8/10 interocular width and slightly less than 4/10 transocular width. Pronotum (
<figureCitation box="[745,847,759,784]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 8" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1892,1915]" captionTargetBox="[288,1361,209,1838]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[205,1368,193,1843]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 8. Portanus restingalis sp. nov. Male holotype: 1, dorsal habitus (antennae and legs not depicted; right forewing partially damaged); 2, head, pronotum, and mesonotum, dorsal view; 3, pygofer, valve and left subgenital plate, lateral view; 4, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view (setae omitted); 5, right style, lateral view; 6, apical portion of right style, dorsal view; 7, connective and aedeagus, lateral view; 8, connective and aedeagus, ventral view. Abbreviations: C = connective, S = shaft of aedeagus, P = process of aedeagus. Scale bars in mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/258152/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="400">Figs 1, 2</figureCitation>
) with width slightly smaller than transocular width. Forewings with three closed anteapical cells; median cell longer than inner and outer ones. Hind legs with femoral setal formula 2:2:1; length of basal tarsomere greater than combined length of two succeeding tarsomeres.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,580,2009]" pageId="1" pageNumber="400">
Male genitalia. Pygofer (
<figureCitation box="[495,569,868,893]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 8" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1892,1915]" captionTargetBox="[288,1361,209,1838]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[205,1368,193,1843]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 8. Portanus restingalis sp. nov. Male holotype: 1, dorsal habitus (antennae and legs not depicted; right forewing partially damaged); 2, head, pronotum, and mesonotum, dorsal view; 3, pygofer, valve and left subgenital plate, lateral view; 4, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view (setae omitted); 5, right style, lateral view; 6, apical portion of right style, dorsal view; 7, connective and aedeagus, lateral view; 8, connective and aedeagus, ventral view. Abbreviations: C = connective, S = shaft of aedeagus, P = process of aedeagus. Scale bars in mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/258152/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="400">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
), in lateral view, short and high; posterior margin broadly rounded with conspicuous, moderately broad dorsal lobe; lobe region with inner digitiform process, longer than lobe; dorsal portion of pygofer with group of long macrosetae extending posteriorly in a row; posterior lobe with short microsetae. Valve (
<figureCitation box="[369,473,975,1000]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 8" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1892,1915]" captionTargetBox="[288,1361,209,1838]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[205,1368,193,1843]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 8. Portanus restingalis sp. nov. Male holotype: 1, dorsal habitus (antennae and legs not depicted; right forewing partially damaged); 2, head, pronotum, and mesonotum, dorsal view; 3, pygofer, valve and left subgenital plate, lateral view; 4, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view (setae omitted); 5, right style, lateral view; 6, apical portion of right style, dorsal view; 7, connective and aedeagus, lateral view; 8, connective and aedeagus, ventral view. Abbreviations: C = connective, S = shaft of aedeagus, P = process of aedeagus. Scale bars in mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/258152/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="400">Figs 3, 4</figureCitation>
) broad, subrectangular, posterior margin straight. Subgenital plates (
<figureCitation box="[1258,1362,975,1000]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 8" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1892,1915]" captionTargetBox="[288,1361,209,1838]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[205,1368,193,1843]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 8. Portanus restingalis sp. nov. Male holotype: 1, dorsal habitus (antennae and legs not depicted; right forewing partially damaged); 2, head, pronotum, and mesonotum, dorsal view; 3, pygofer, valve and left subgenital plate, lateral view; 4, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view (setae omitted); 5, right style, lateral view; 6, apical portion of right style, dorsal view; 7, connective and aedeagus, lateral view; 8, connective and aedeagus, ventral view. Abbreviations: C = connective, S = shaft of aedeagus, P = process of aedeagus. Scale bars in mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/258152/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="400">Figs 3, 4</figureCitation>
) long, extending posteriorly well beyond pygofer apex; narrowed on apical half; basal third with emargination on outer margin; apex rounded; ventral longitudinal row of long macrosetae; dorsal area with long microsetae; apical margin with row of microsetae. Style (
<figureCitation box="[589,691,1084,1109]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 8" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1892,1915]" captionTargetBox="[288,1361,209,1838]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[205,1368,193,1843]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 8. Portanus restingalis sp. nov. Male holotype: 1, dorsal habitus (antennae and legs not depicted; right forewing partially damaged); 2, head, pronotum, and mesonotum, dorsal view; 3, pygofer, valve and left subgenital plate, lateral view; 4, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view (setae omitted); 5, right style, lateral view; 6, apical portion of right style, dorsal view; 7, connective and aedeagus, lateral view; 8, connective and aedeagus, ventral view. Abbreviations: C = connective, S = shaft of aedeagus, P = process of aedeagus. Scale bars in mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/258152/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="400">Figs 5, 6</figureCitation>
) long and narrow, extending posteriorly beyond connective apex; apical portion broad in lateral view; preapical lobe moderately produced; apex long and acute, curved outwards, forming hook with preapical lobe. Connective (
<figureCitation box="[719,830,1156,1181]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 8" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1892,1915]" captionTargetBox="[288,1361,209,1838]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[205,1368,193,1843]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 8. Portanus restingalis sp. nov. Male holotype: 1, dorsal habitus (antennae and legs not depicted; right forewing partially damaged); 2, head, pronotum, and mesonotum, dorsal view; 3, pygofer, valve and left subgenital plate, lateral view; 4, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view (setae omitted); 5, right style, lateral view; 6, apical portion of right style, dorsal view; 7, connective and aedeagus, lateral view; 8, connective and aedeagus, ventral view. Abbreviations: C = connective, S = shaft of aedeagus, P = process of aedeagus. Scale bars in mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/258152/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="400">Figs 7, 8</figureCitation>
) Y-shaped in ventral view; arms moderately long; anteromedian margin with lobe; apical portion broadened in ventral view. Aedeagus (
<figureCitation box="[1123,1224,1191,1216]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 8" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1892,1915]" captionTargetBox="[288,1361,209,1838]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[205,1368,193,1843]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 8. Portanus restingalis sp. nov. Male holotype: 1, dorsal habitus (antennae and legs not depicted; right forewing partially damaged); 2, head, pronotum, and mesonotum, dorsal view; 3, pygofer, valve and left subgenital plate, lateral view; 4, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view (setae omitted); 5, right style, lateral view; 6, apical portion of right style, dorsal view; 7, connective and aedeagus, lateral view; 8, connective and aedeagus, ventral view. Abbreviations: C = connective, S = shaft of aedeagus, P = process of aedeagus. Scale bars in mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/258152/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="400">Figs 7, 8</figureCitation>
) long and narrow; shaft slightly sinuous; apical portion slightly broadened; median ventral portion of shaft with basally articulated, bifid long process, extending posteriorly beyond shaft apex; rami of process narrowing apically, symmetrical and parallel in ventral view.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,580,2009]" pageId="1" pageNumber="400">
Color. Dorsum (
<figureCitation box="[380,480,1335,1360]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 8" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1892,1915]" captionTargetBox="[288,1361,209,1838]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[205,1368,193,1843]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 8. Portanus restingalis sp. nov. Male holotype: 1, dorsal habitus (antennae and legs not depicted; right forewing partially damaged); 2, head, pronotum, and mesonotum, dorsal view; 3, pygofer, valve and left subgenital plate, lateral view; 4, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view (setae omitted); 5, right style, lateral view; 6, apical portion of right style, dorsal view; 7, connective and aedeagus, lateral view; 8, connective and aedeagus, ventral view. Abbreviations: C = connective, S = shaft of aedeagus, P = process of aedeagus. Scale bars in mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/258152/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="400">Figs 1, 2</figureCitation>
) brownish-yellow with ivory areas; narrow, irregular orange median stripe extending from anterior portion of crown to scutoscutellar suture of mesonotum. Crown (
<figureCitation box="[1063,1168,1372,1397]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 8" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1892,1915]" captionTargetBox="[288,1361,209,1838]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[205,1368,193,1843]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 8. Portanus restingalis sp. nov. Male holotype: 1, dorsal habitus (antennae and legs not depicted; right forewing partially damaged); 2, head, pronotum, and mesonotum, dorsal view; 3, pygofer, valve and left subgenital plate, lateral view; 4, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view (setae omitted); 5, right style, lateral view; 6, apical portion of right style, dorsal view; 7, connective and aedeagus, lateral view; 8, connective and aedeagus, ventral view. Abbreviations: C = connective, S = shaft of aedeagus, P = process of aedeagus. Scale bars in mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/258152/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="400">Figs 1, 2</figureCitation>
) with apical transverse ivory band on ocelli region; two conspicuous transverse dark brown stripes, one below and one above ocelli; pair of transverse ivory marks located medially behind superior dark brown stripe. Ocelli yellowish-white. Eyes brown. Pronotum (
<figureCitation box="[277,379,1479,1504]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 8" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1892,1915]" captionTargetBox="[288,1361,209,1838]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[205,1368,193,1843]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 8. Portanus restingalis sp. nov. Male holotype: 1, dorsal habitus (antennae and legs not depicted; right forewing partially damaged); 2, head, pronotum, and mesonotum, dorsal view; 3, pygofer, valve and left subgenital plate, lateral view; 4, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view (setae omitted); 5, right style, lateral view; 6, apical portion of right style, dorsal view; 7, connective and aedeagus, lateral view; 8, connective and aedeagus, ventral view. Abbreviations: C = connective, S = shaft of aedeagus, P = process of aedeagus. Scale bars in mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/258152/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="400">Figs 1, 2</figureCitation>
) with pair of oblique, faint brown maculae on anterior half of disc; pair of orange areas near humeral angles. Forewings (
<figureCitation box="[470,534,1516,1541]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 8" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1892,1915]" captionTargetBox="[288,1361,209,1838]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[205,1368,193,1843]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 8. Portanus restingalis sp. nov. Male holotype: 1, dorsal habitus (antennae and legs not depicted; right forewing partially damaged); 2, head, pronotum, and mesonotum, dorsal view; 3, pygofer, valve and left subgenital plate, lateral view; 4, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view (setae omitted); 5, right style, lateral view; 6, apical portion of right style, dorsal view; 7, connective and aedeagus, lateral view; 8, connective and aedeagus, ventral view. Abbreviations: C = connective, S = shaft of aedeagus, P = process of aedeagus. Scale bars in mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/258152/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="400">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
) translucent; veins mostly yellowish-brown; clavus and basal portion of corium with pale yellowish-brown areas; corium with brown macula near costal margin, approximately opposite apex of clavus; basal veins of apical cells marked with brown; apical portion of apical cells slightly darkened. Face pale yellow; apical portion of labium dark brown. Thoracic sclerites pale yellow laterally and ventrally. Legs pale yellow with apices of tarsi dark brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,580,2009]" box="[199,400,1695,1720]" pageId="1" pageNumber="400">Female unknown.</paragraph>
