<subSubSection lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="402" pageId="1" pageNumber="400" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,580,2009]" lastBlockId="3.[151,1436,151,285]" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="402" pageId="1" pageNumber="400">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1876,1901]" pageId="1" pageNumber="400">Remarks.</emphasis>
The new species is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Carvalho &amp; Cavichioli, 2003" authorityName="Carvalho &amp; Cavichioli" authorityYear="2003" box="[653,1222,1876,1901]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Portanus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="400" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="marginatus">
<emphasis box="[653,889,1877,1900]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="400">Portanus marginatus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Carvalho" box="[897,1222,1876,1901]" pageId="1" pageNumber="400" refString="Carvalho, A. N. &amp; Cavichioli, R. R. (2003) Portanus Ball: descricoes de dez especies novas (Hemiptera, Cicadellidae, Xestocephalinae). Revista Brasileira de Entomologia, 47 (4), 547 - 558. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1590 / s 0085 - 56262003000400003" type="journal article" year="2003">
Carvalho &amp; Cavichioli, 
<quantity box="[1166,1222,1876,1900]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.087619999999999" pageId="1" pageNumber="400" unit="in" value="2003.0">2003</quantity>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
in some aspects of the color pattern and male genital structures. Both species have yellow to orange ground color and the anterior margin of the crown with transverse dark brown to black stripes (
<figureCitation box="[893,997,1948,1973]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 8" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1892,1915]" captionTargetBox="[288,1361,209,1838]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[205,1368,193,1843]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 8. Portanus restingalis sp. nov. Male holotype: 1, dorsal habitus (antennae and legs not depicted; right forewing partially damaged); 2, head, pronotum, and mesonotum, dorsal view; 3, pygofer, valve and left subgenital plate, lateral view; 4, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view (setae omitted); 5, right style, lateral view; 6, apical portion of right style, dorsal view; 7, connective and aedeagus, lateral view; 8, connective and aedeagus, ventral view. Abbreviations: C = connective, S = shaft of aedeagus, P = process of aedeagus. Scale bars in mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/258152/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="400">Figs 1, 2</figureCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Carvalho" box="[1010,1335,1948,1973]" pageId="1" pageNumber="400" refString="Carvalho, A. N. &amp; Cavichioli, R. R. (2003) Portanus Ball: descricoes de dez especies novas (Hemiptera, Cicadellidae, Xestocephalinae). Revista Brasileira de Entomologia, 47 (4), 547 - 558. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1590 / s 0085 - 56262003000400003" type="journal article" year="2003">Carvalho &amp; Cavichioli 2003</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 8a). The pygofer is short, with a dorsoapical rounded lobe and inner narrow process, which is short and rounded apically (
<figureCitation box="[258,330,151,176]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 8" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1892,1915]" captionTargetBox="[288,1361,209,1838]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[205,1368,193,1843]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 8. Portanus restingalis sp. nov. Male holotype: 1, dorsal habitus (antennae and legs not depicted; right forewing partially damaged); 2, head, pronotum, and mesonotum, dorsal view; 3, pygofer, valve and left subgenital plate, lateral view; 4, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view (setae omitted); 5, right style, lateral view; 6, apical portion of right style, dorsal view; 7, connective and aedeagus, lateral view; 8, connective and aedeagus, ventral view. Abbreviations: C = connective, S = shaft of aedeagus, P = process of aedeagus. Scale bars in mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/258152/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="402">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Carvalho" box="[346,678,151,176]" pageId="3" pageNumber="402" refString="Carvalho, A. N. &amp; Cavichioli, R. R. (2003) Portanus Ball: descricoes de dez especies novas (Hemiptera, Cicadellidae, Xestocephalinae). Revista Brasileira de Entomologia, 47 (4), 547 - 558. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1590 / s 0085 - 56262003000400003" type="journal article" year="2003">Carvalho &amp; Cavichioli 2003</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 8c). However, the new species has a pair of transverse dark brown stripes anteriorly, one above and one below the ocelli, extending from eye to eye without interruption (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 8" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1892,1915]" captionTargetBox="[288,1361,209,1838]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[205,1368,193,1843]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 8. Portanus restingalis sp. nov. Male holotype: 1, dorsal habitus (antennae and legs not depicted; right forewing partially damaged); 2, head, pronotum, and mesonotum, dorsal view; 3, pygofer, valve and left subgenital plate, lateral view; 4, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view (setae omitted); 5, right style, lateral view; 6, apical portion of right style, dorsal view; 7, connective and aedeagus, lateral view; 8, connective and aedeagus, ventral view. Abbreviations: C = connective, S = shaft of aedeagus, P = process of aedeagus. Scale bars in mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/258152/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="402">Figs 1, 2</figureCitation>
). The aedeagus has ventrally a basally articulated, bifid long process (
<figureCitation box="[1047,1157,223,248]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 8" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1892,1915]" captionTargetBox="[288,1361,209,1838]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[205,1368,193,1843]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 8. Portanus restingalis sp. nov. Male holotype: 1, dorsal habitus (antennae and legs not depicted; right forewing partially damaged); 2, head, pronotum, and mesonotum, dorsal view; 3, pygofer, valve and left subgenital plate, lateral view; 4, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view (setae omitted); 5, right style, lateral view; 6, apical portion of right style, dorsal view; 7, connective and aedeagus, lateral view; 8, connective and aedeagus, ventral view. Abbreviations: C = connective, S = shaft of aedeagus, P = process of aedeagus. Scale bars in mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/258152/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="402">Figs 7, 8</figureCitation>
), which is absent in 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Portanus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="402" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="marginatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="402">P. marginatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Carvalho" box="[291,702,260,285]" pageId="3" pageNumber="402" refString="Carvalho, A. N. &amp; Cavichioli, R. R. (2003) Portanus Ball: descricoes de dez especies novas (Hemiptera, Cicadellidae, Xestocephalinae). Revista Brasileira de Entomologia, 47 (4), 547 - 558. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1590 / s 0085 - 56262003000400003" type="journal article" year="2003" yearSuffix="g">
Carvalho &amp; Cavichioli 2003: fig. 
<quantity box="[671,702,260,284]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="kg" metricValue="8.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="402" unit="g" value="8.0">8g</quantity>
</bibRefCitation>
).
